{
  "text": "It can be proven in at least two different ways that the map D a \u2192 \u0393 k(x) maps the\u1e90(1)-conjugacy classes of sections of (6) injectively into the set of \u0393k (X) -conjugacy classes of sections of (5), see for example [CITATION_1] Section 1.4, or [24] Section 1.3 and Theorem 14+17, or [CITATION_2] . The birational form of the section conjecture speculates that for a smooth, projective geometrically connected curve the map from k-rational points to packets of sections of (5) is bijective and that there are no other sections of (5), see [CITATION_3] ",
  "correct_citation": {
